  "prompt": "What should be my individual subject scores in NEET 2017?",
  "response": "In the NEET 2017 exam, your individual subject scores will vary depending on your performance in each subject. However, it's important to note the exam structure and marking scheme, which are as follows:\n\n1. The NEET exam consists of three subjects: Physics, Chemistry, and Biology (Biology includes Botany and Zoology).\n2. The total number of questions is 180, with 45 questions each for Physics and Chemistry, and 90 questions for Biology.\n3. Each question carries 4 marks, so the total possible score is 720.\n4. For every incorrect answer, 1 mark is deducted as a penalty.\n\nYour individual subject scores will depend on how many questions you answer correctly in each subject and how many you get wrong. To calculate your scores:\n- Multiply the number of correct answers in each subject by 4.\n- Deduct the penalty for any incorrect answers (1 mark per incorrect answer).\n\nYour performance in each subject should align with your preparation and understanding, so focus on areas where you excel and work on improving areas where you are weaker. Aim for a balanced score across all subjects to maximize your overall performance in the NEET exam.",
